# Tech Stack: Scaffolded Application

This is a guideline. Only when applicable for this project use preferred technology description as described below

## Core Infrastructure

- **Monorepo Structure**: Using Turborepo for managing a multi-package architecture
- **Package Manager**: Bun (v1.2.2)
- **Node.js**: Version 20+
- **TypeScript**: For type safety across the entire codebase

## Frontend

- **Framework option 1**: Next.js 15+ with React 19
- **Framework option 2**: ViteJS with React 19
- **UI Components**: Custom UI library built on top of Shadcn primitives (using Radix)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with custom configuration
- **State Management**: Combination of React Query for server state, React Context for dataprovider, useLocalStorage for persisted state, React hooks for local state
- **Form Handling**: React Hook Form with Zod for validation

## Backend

- **Runtime**: Bun
- **API Framework**: Elysia.js (lightweight, type-safe HTTP framework)
- **Architecture**: Service-oriented with microservices approach
- **API Documentation**: Swagger via @elysiajs/swagger

## Data Layer

- **Database**: MongoDB with replica set configuration. using Prisma as ORM
- **Search**: Elasticsearch
- **Caching**: Redis
- **Data Access**: Custom service packages for data operations

## AI/ML Components

- **AI Services**: Custom AI implementation with specialized services
- **Memory/Sequential Processing**: Custom AI processing servers

## Authentication

- **Auth Provider**: WorkOS integration for authentication
- **Token Handling**: JWT (via jose library)

## DevOps

- **Containerization**: Docker with docker-compose
- **CI Pipeline**: Likely using Turbo for build optimization
- **Deployment**: Railway.app (based on configuration files)

## Testing & Quality

- **Testing Framework**: Vitest with browser capabilities
- **Component Testing**: Storybook for UI component development
- **Linting**: ESLint with custom configuration
- **Formatting**: Prettier

## Notable Libraries

- **UI Components**: Shadcn, Framer Motion, Lucide React
- **Date Handling**: date-fns (/fp)
- **Functional Programming**: ramda (/fp)
- **API Communication**: @elysiajs/eden for type-safe API clients
- **Markdown**: React Markdown with remark-gfm

The application follows a modern, functional approach with a strong emphasis on type safety, component reusability, and service-oriented architecture.
